The paper discusses interactive tools for searching for preferred items, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of preference models and suggestions for improving the search process suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of user preferences and hidden preferences may involve database techniques (cs.DB). Finally, the evaluation of the performance of the techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
